type: web_research
title: LLM Model Landscape 2026 - Comprehensive Research
key_insights[10]: "GLM-4.7: 358B params, LiveCodeBench 84.9%, SWE-bench 73.8%, open-source. GLM-5 expected Feb 2026.","DeepSeek R1: reasoning model, V3.2 leads open-source SWE-bench at 73.0%. Ultra-low pricing $0.28/$0.42 per 1M tokens.","Qwen3-Coder-Next: 80B params, 3B active (MoE), SWE-bench 70.6%, Apache 2.0, runs locally.","Qwen3-Coder-480B: 480B total, 35B active, top-tier performance.","Claude Opus 4.5: SWE-bench 80.9% (top), $5/$25 per 1M tokens. Sonnet 4.5: $3/$15. Haiku 4.5: $1/$5.","GPT-4.1: $2/$8 per 1M tokens. o3: $2/$8. o4-mini: $1.10/$4.40.","Gemini 2.5 Pro: $1.25/$10 per 1M tokens. Flash: $0.15/$0.60. Flash-Lite: even cheaper.","Kimi K2.5: first open-weight model trained on 15T tokens, multi-agent capable, released Jan 2026.","OpenRouter: 18 free models, 50 req/day free tier. DeepSeek V3.2 beats GPT-4 at 1/40th cost.","Local Mac: Qwen 32B excellent on 64GB RAM. 7B models ~20 tok/s on M2, 70B ~5-8 tok/s."
findings[6]: "SWE-bench top: Claude Opus 4.5 (80.9%), Opus 4.6 (80.8%), GPT-5.2 (80.0%), Gemini 3 Flash (78.0%)","Open-source SWE-bench top: DeepSeek V3.2 (73.0%), GLM-4.7 (73.8%), Qwen3-Coder-Next (70.6%)",LLM inference prices fallen 50x per year median,"Chinese open-source models (DeepSeek, Qwen, GLM, Kimi) dominate open-source frontier","Translation best: Claude for literary, GPT-5.1 for general, Qwen-MT for CJK, Gemini for multimodal docs","Summarization best: Qwen3-30B-A3B, GLM-4.5V, GPT-OSS-120B"
